At 05:21 PM 04/12/2002, you wrote:

>Actually, the filter is full of a fine bronze or copper steel wool that
>doesn't rust, but it does cake and get blocked up with carbon- I cut one
>apart that was rusted through.  I suspect you could buy a spool of very
>fine wire (armature wire?) and ball it up and stuff a can and make one!

Go to any grocer or hardware store and get copper scouring pads. Exactly 
the type of stuff for this restoration. Bronse wool in a heavy grade would 
also do the job. Find this at marinas where they use a lot of it for 
maintenance on ships and boats.

